1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the optimization of the secrecy rate, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on multihop wireless networks and routing strategies, which are key topics in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with secure transmission and eavesdropping, which are core topics in cryptography and security. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions simulation results, which may involve multimedia data transmission. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a revised Bellman-Ford algorithm for solving the secure routing problem, which is related to systems and control.
